# AI Study Hub / SWP391 OpenCode Instructions

## Canonical project

- Repository: `D:\FPT\summer2026\SWP391\AI-Study-Hub-v2`
- Solution: `AI_Study_Hub_v2\AI_Study_Hub_v2.sln`
- Project documentation: `..\Project-Docs`
- Durable handoffs: `..\Project-Docs\sessions`
- Historical project notes: `previous_session`

Never infer project state from chat memory. Verify files, Git state, and saved session notes.

## Mandatory session bootstrap

At the start of every new session:

1. Read `PROJECT_MEMORY.md` and `_CURRENT_SESSION.md` (also injected by `opencode.json`).
2. Read the newest relevant handoff from `..\Project-Docs\sessions` when `_CURRENT_SESSION.md` is missing, stale, or closed.
3. Run `git branch --show-current` and `git status --short --branch --untracked-files=all`.
4. Reconcile any mismatch between saved notes and the working tree before editing.
5. Select only the skills needed for the current task.

The commands `/resume-swp` and `/handoff-swp` implement this protocol.

## Agent team

The source of truth is the global `oh-my-opencode-slim.json` preset `aibox`.

- `orchestrator`: plans and delegates.
- `explorer`: searches the repository and maps code paths.
- `librarian`: documentation and external research.
- `oracle`: architecture, debugging, and high-judgment review.
- `designer`: UI/UX and visual implementation guidance.
- `fixer`: focused implementation and repairs.
- `observer`: screenshots, PDFs, and other visual evidence.

Do not recreate these agents inside a chat. Delegate to the configured agents when their specialty applies.

## Skill routing

- Start project work with `aistudy`.
- Use `one-command-continue` when the user says `tiếp tục SWP` or equivalent.
- Use `existing-project` for scoped code changes in the existing solution.
- Use `ui-progress` for UI inventory and prioritized UI backlog.
- Use `role-audit` for role/permission comparisons.
- Use `external-test-tools` for Postman, browser, security, load, or external verification.
- Use `codemap` for broad repository mapping and `deepwork` only for genuinely complex multi-step work.

Do not activate every skill at once. Choose one primary workflow and only the supporting skills it requires.

## Session persistence

- `_CURRENT_SESSION.md` is the live recovery point. Update it after meaningful edits, decisions, tests, failures, or completed milestones.
- Keep logs evidence-based and never include secrets.
- On pause or close, update `_CURRENT_SESSION.md` and write a dated handoff under `..\Project-Docs\sessions`.
- Do not modify closed historical handoffs; write a new handoff or correction.

## Safety

- Preserve all uncommitted work unless the user explicitly authorizes a revert.
- Do not print, commit, or copy secrets from `.env`, user-secrets, tokens, or credentials.
- Ask before destructive migrations, data deletion, reset, force operations, push, merge, rebase, or deployment.
- Do not commit or push unless explicitly requested.

## Technical direction

- .NET 8, ASP.NET Core, Blazor/MudBlazor, EF Core, PostgreSQL/pgvector, Supabase, and RAG services.
- Preserve existing API and backend contracts during UI work.
- Keep the premium dark purple/cyan glass visual direction and existing glow/orb motif.
- Prefer focused incremental edits over broad rewrites.

## Common checks

Run from the repository root:

```powershell
git status --short --branch --untracked-files=all
dotnet build "AI_Study_Hub_v2\AI_Study_Hub_v2.sln" --nologo
dotnet test "AI_Study_Hub_v2\AI_Study_Hub_v2.sln" --nologo --no-build
Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 5240 -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
```
